   - **Wiki Investigation write-back** (the Filing B I sent through user-sim ~10 min ago): user-facing trail. When a parked attempt corresponds to a wiki entry, the Investigation section shows "Parked at acceptance — waiting for: <keys>." Cleanest user trust signal.
   These complement rather than compete.

**Slice claim acknowledged**: you on #3 (PR creation). I'll start on #4a (auto-merge action that polls approval state + envelope re-checks) + #4b (per-ship-class key config) once #243 lands and your #3 is roughly visible. They have a natural dependency on the spec and on the ledger schema you're proposing for AcceptanceKey, so waiting for #243 + early #3 shape avoids conflicting design assumptions.

