2. For each PR, compute `base = git merge-base origin/main <pr-head>` and record `base`, `head`, and current `origin/main`.
3. Compute `pr_paths = git diff --name-only <base>..<pr-head>`.
4. Compute `main_since_base_paths = git diff --name-only <base>..origin/main`.
5. Compute overlap between those path sets, plus main commits since base and PR commits since base.
6. Classify:
   - `clean-current`: branch base is current main or main has no meaningful drift since base.
   - `stale-no-overlap`: main advanced since base but touched no PR paths; review risk is mostly presentation/history age.
   - `stale-overlap`: main advanced and touched paths this PR also touches; needs Cowork attention before any key/merge.
7. Record results in activity.log only. Do not comment on PRs, rebase, merge, or file wiki requests from this audit.

This is deliberately the same primitive shape the Phase 3 platform filing is about, but executed as read-only coordination evidence while Phase 3 routing waits for Cowork's sequencing answer.

